260
00:16:51,440 --> 00:16:52,510
Sit down.

261
00:16:56,640 --> 00:16:58,280
Dong-cheol. Dong-cheol.

262
00:16:58,550 --> 00:16:59,950
Isn't this fate?

263
00:17:02,780 --> 00:17:04,550
Everyone, be quiet.

264
00:17:06,089 --> 00:17:07,960
She'll feel awkward
since she's from Seoul,

265
00:17:08,020 --> 00:17:10,290
so I want all of you to be friendly
towards her. Okay?

266
00:17:10,359 --> 00:17:11,460
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

267
00:17:11,530 --> 00:17:12,930
Say something to your friends.

268
00:17:16,760 --> 00:17:18,500
My name is Im Sang-mi.

269
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:22,000
-My gosh.
-Listen to her accent.

270
00:17:22,069 --> 00:17:23,400
Haven't you ever heard
a Seoul accent before?

271
00:17:23,470 --> 00:17:25,069
Stop acting like
you're from the countryside.

272
00:17:25,140 --> 00:17:26,210
Sang-hwan.

273
00:17:26,540 --> 00:17:27,480
Yes, ma'am.

274
00:17:27,540 --> 00:17:28,840
Do you see the empty seat
next to him?

275
00:17:28,910 --> 00:17:30,750
That's your seat.
You can go sit there.

276
00:17:32,810 --> 00:17:34,280
-My gosh.
-I'm so envious.

277
00:17:34,650 --> 00:17:37,080
-You're so lucky.
-I can't believe this.

278
00:17:39,350 --> 00:17:40,720
-Sang-hwan.
-Yes?

279
00:17:40,790 --> 00:17:42,490
-You can sit back down.
-Okay, ma'am.

280
00:17:44,230 --> 00:17:45,830
Where did we finish off yesterday?

281
00:18:16,560 --> 00:18:20,130
(Have you been doing well?)

282
00:18:49,290 --> 00:18:51,830
Let's eat together, my friend.

283
00:18:51,890 --> 00:18:53,460
It won't taste good like this.

284
00:18:53,530 --> 00:18:57,060
Here. It'll taste better
if you mix everything like this.

285
00:18:57,770 --> 00:18:59,430
Here's the finale.

286
00:19:02,670 --> 00:19:05,240
Now, this is what you call dog food.

287
00:19:07,510 --> 00:19:08,440
Hurry up and eat.

288
00:19:08,510 --> 00:19:09,780
Well, I--

289
00:19:09,840 --> 00:19:11,550
Hurry up and eat your lunch.

290
00:19:15,680 --> 00:19:16,750
Hey!

291
00:19:25,790 --> 00:19:26,860
Eat.

292
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:31,330
Hey, I said eat your lunch!

293
00:19:51,120 --> 00:19:52,590
Hey!

294
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:56,360
What was that?

295
00:20:00,430 --> 00:20:02,400
-Apologize to him.
-Who are you?

296
00:20:02,630 --> 00:20:04,630
Are you his girlfriend or what?

297
00:20:04,700 --> 00:20:06,770
If you don't apologize this instant,
I'll report you to the police.

298
00:20:06,830 --> 00:20:10,670
Oh, she must be his sister.

299
00:20:10,740 --> 00:20:13,640
-Sister?
-I heard he has a twin sister.

300
00:20:13,940 --> 00:20:15,210
It must be her.

301
00:20:16,210 --> 00:20:18,410
Hey, is she your sister?

302
00:20:22,580 --> 00:20:24,750
Is that so? Then

303
00:20:25,020 --> 00:20:26,490
give me money
to get this dry-cleaned first.

304
00:20:26,550 --> 00:20:27,960
You guys harassed him first.

305
00:20:28,020 --> 00:20:29,090
Do you have proof?

306
00:20:29,660 --> 00:20:32,260
Guys, if any of you

307
00:20:32,330 --> 00:20:36,200
saw me harassing this idiot,
come forward. Now!

308
00:20:36,900 --> 00:20:38,370
I said come forward now!

309
00:20:38,430 --> 00:20:40,470
Say something. All of you saw it!

310
00:20:41,570 --> 00:20:42,900
This girl is funny.

311
00:20:44,470 --> 00:20:45,470
Hey.

312
00:20:46,470 --> 00:20:47,710
Do you want to be my girlfriend?

313
00:20:48,980 --> 00:20:50,080
I'll be nice to you.

314
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:54,380
-Did you see that?
-Is she out of her mind?

315
00:20:54,480 --> 00:20:55,880
Hey, have you lost your mind?

316
00:20:57,590 --> 00:20:59,190
Hey, are you crazy?

317
00:20:59,250 --> 00:21:00,290
Hey!

318
00:21:06,290 --> 00:21:07,630
You're embarrassing all of us.

319
00:21:09,230 --> 00:21:12,500
If you come any closer,
I'll beat up all of you to a pulp.

320
00:21:13,230 --> 00:21:15,370
Hey, do you know whom
you're dealing with here?

321
00:21:15,440 --> 00:21:17,740
Are you both insane or what?

322
00:21:18,410 --> 00:21:20,070
I have the strongest punch
in the entire school.

323
00:21:20,140 --> 00:21:21,840
-Oh, is that so?
-You do?

324
00:21:21,910 --> 00:21:23,940
What kind of punch? Fruit punch?

325
00:21:24,010 --> 00:21:25,380
-Rum punch?
-Slush punch?

326
00:21:25,450 --> 00:21:27,410
-My gosh.
-Aren't I so witty?

327
00:21:29,620 --> 00:21:30,790
Are you guys confident?

328
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:33,120
Then shall we have a showdown?

329
00:21:33,190 --> 00:21:34,190
(HAN SANG-HWAN)

330
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:38,690
Dong-seok, let's just go.

331
00:21:38,760 --> 00:21:41,500
What are you talking about?
I'll teach them a serious lesson.

332
00:21:41,560 --> 00:21:43,930
It's not that.
He's Han Sang-hwan.

333
00:21:44,870 --> 00:21:46,200
Who's Han Sang-hwan?

334
00:21:48,340 --> 00:21:50,300
What are you whispering
to each other?

335
00:21:52,910 --> 00:21:55,510
That bell saved your lives today.

336
00:21:55,740 --> 00:21:57,280
I'll see you both soon.
You got that?

337
00:21:58,480 --> 00:21:59,710
Let go, you idiot.

338
00:21:59,780 --> 00:22:01,550
-I said, let go.
-All right, see you around.

339
00:22:01,880 --> 00:22:03,920
-What's his problem?
-Who knows?

340
00:22:05,390 --> 00:22:07,420
-Are you guys all right?
-Yes.

341
00:22:07,490 --> 00:22:10,690
Those jerks will bother you guys again.
You should tell your teacher.

342
00:22:12,930 --> 00:22:14,660
Can't you hear me? Those jerks--

343
00:22:14,730 --> 00:22:18,030
Thanks for your help today,
but we'll figure out what to do.

344
00:22:27,140 --> 00:22:28,780
-Watch me, okay?
-Just shoot it.

345
00:22:28,840 --> 00:22:30,740
-Wait. Hold on a second.
-Pass me the ball.

346
00:22:30,980 --> 00:22:32,110
Here you go.

347
00:22:32,180 --> 00:22:33,950
-Hey, guys.
-Hey.

348
00:22:34,110 --> 00:22:38,020
I heard you guys had a fight
with that bully during lunch break.

349
00:22:38,550 --> 00:22:41,760
We didn't fight. He ran away as
soon as he heard Sang-hwan's name.

350
00:22:41,820 --> 00:22:42,820
That's correct.

351
00:22:43,490 --> 00:22:46,630
Nice. You sure are the son
of the future governor.

352
00:22:46,860 --> 00:22:49,660
He's definitely not like us
lowborn people. You lowlife.

353
00:22:51,500 --> 00:22:52,500
You slave.

354
00:22:52,570 --> 00:22:54,740
-Lowlife Choe Man-hui.
-Slave Woo Jeong-hun.

355
00:22:54,800 --> 00:22:56,600
-Do you want a showdown?
-At the internet cafe?

356
00:22:57,300 --> 00:23:01,310
You read my mind.
This guy can really pick up hints.

357
00:23:02,480 --> 00:23:04,480
I'm sorry, but I don't think
I can join you guys today.

358
00:23:04,810 --> 00:23:06,450
-Bye.
-Hey, wait.

359
00:23:06,980 --> 00:23:08,750
We can't split into teams
of two without you.

360
00:23:09,620 --> 00:23:11,520
Learn to take a hint, you blockhead.

361
00:23:12,120 --> 00:23:13,620
-Okay, bye.
-Sorry. See you.

362
00:23:16,160 --> 00:23:17,390
I'll be off too.

363
00:23:18,390 --> 00:23:19,530
Is something up?

364
00:23:22,460 --> 00:23:23,800
It's your mom's birthday, right?

365
00:23:26,900 --> 00:23:29,170
Hey, pull those shoulders back, okay?

366
00:23:30,400 --> 00:23:32,040
You idiot. Fix your shoulders first.

367
00:23:32,940 --> 00:23:34,880
-Pull back your shoulders, jerk.
-Gosh.

368
00:23:35,480 --> 00:23:37,340
I told you to fix yours first.

369
00:23:44,290 --> 00:23:46,650
(MUJI HIGH SCHOOL)

370
00:23:50,990 --> 00:23:52,030
Sang-mi.

371
00:23:54,730 --> 00:23:56,960
I was in the area for my volunteer work.

372
00:23:57,030 --> 00:24:00,800
I stopped by just in case
and saw you two walking out.

373
00:24:01,100 --> 00:24:05,510
Oh, right. Apostle Kang said
she has to give you guys something.

374
00:24:05,710 --> 00:24:07,780
You have time
to stop by Guseonwon, right?

375
00:24:08,210 --> 00:24:09,240
Pardon me?

376
00:24:13,110 --> 00:24:15,680
-Yes, we do.
-All right. Let's go, then.

377
00:24:39,010 --> 00:24:44,510
(Thanks for always being by my side.
Your man, Han Yong-min)

378
00:24:52,350 --> 00:24:53,450
Mom.

379
00:24:54,620 --> 00:24:56,020
Get better and come home soon.

380
00:24:57,460 --> 00:24:58,690
Dad and I are

381
00:24:59,890 --> 00:25:01,630
waiting for you.

382
00:25:07,030 --> 00:25:09,800
I'm not sure if I can accept this.

383
00:25:10,340 --> 00:25:13,310
I'll call my dad
and ask him if it's okay to--

384
00:25:15,540 --> 00:25:16,910
Are you really going to be like this?

385
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:20,510
-Sorry?
-You should know how to accept

386
00:25:20,810 --> 00:25:22,520
a gesture of sincere kindness.

387
00:25:24,920 --> 00:25:28,460
Oh, I apologize if I hurt your feelings.

388
00:25:28,720 --> 00:25:30,720
I wasn't sure
because this looks expensive.

389
00:25:35,230 --> 00:25:36,530
You didn't hurt my feelings.

390
00:25:37,000 --> 00:25:41,000
Our faith for Almighty makes us
a community that shares everything.

391
00:25:41,070 --> 00:25:44,870
I'd love it if you could let
your guard down and accept us now.

392
00:25:45,940 --> 00:25:47,140
You can do that, right?

393
00:25:48,740 --> 00:25:49,740
Yes.

394
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:53,280
Please. Please answer my prayer.

395
00:25:53,880 --> 00:25:55,380
I'm having such a hard time.

396
00:25:55,820 --> 00:25:58,150
I can't go on like this any longer.

397
00:25:59,420 --> 00:26:02,260
I just want to live normally
like other kids do.

398
00:26:03,490 --> 00:26:06,130
So please answer my prayer.

399
00:26:16,300 --> 00:26:17,540
I'm sorry.

400
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:19,470
I thought no one was around.

401
00:26:19,740 --> 00:26:21,010
It's okay.

402
00:26:21,640 --> 00:26:23,180
Almighty's grace is

403
00:26:23,240 --> 00:26:26,510
always open to anyone.

404
00:26:27,510 --> 00:26:29,380
Okay. I should go.

405
00:26:32,790 --> 00:26:34,050
Sang-jin.

406
00:26:36,920 --> 00:26:38,960
If I tell you that there's a way
to be free from pain,

407
00:26:39,990 --> 00:26:41,160
will you believe me?

408
00:26:43,060 --> 00:26:46,630
-Pardon me?
-Almighty said that we can be

409
00:26:47,270 --> 00:26:50,670
saved from pain when
we wholeheartedly believe him

410
00:26:51,210 --> 00:26:55,440
and pray instead of relying on our will.

411
00:27:01,980 --> 00:27:04,650
(WAY TO SALVATION)

412
00:27:12,790 --> 00:27:13,930
Sang-jin.

413
00:27:16,800 --> 00:27:17,930
Sang-jin.

414
00:27:34,450 --> 00:27:37,480
(The phone is turned off.
You'll be connected to voice mail.)

415
00:27:37,550 --> 00:27:39,720
(Please leave a message
after the beep.)

416
00:27:40,020 --> 00:27:43,290
(Those who wholeheartedly
believe will be blessed.)

417
00:28:51,090 --> 00:28:52,530
(INDIVIDUAL PRAYER ROOM)

418
00:29:28,100 --> 00:29:32,770
(INDIVIDUAL PRAYER ROOM)

419
00:29:54,390 --> 00:29:55,590
What are you doing here?

420
00:29:57,060 --> 00:30:00,130
I couldn't find my brother.

421
00:30:02,400 --> 00:30:03,500
Really?

422
00:30:05,230 --> 00:30:06,270
Yes.

423
00:30:10,940 --> 00:30:13,970
Do you have something to say to me?

424
00:30:23,880 --> 00:30:25,450
Your skin feels so soft.

425
00:30:32,530 --> 00:30:33,690
There's no need to be surprised.

426
00:30:34,490 --> 00:30:36,030
It's a place where our devoted believers

427
00:30:36,700 --> 00:30:38,800
with deep pain come to

428
00:30:39,500 --> 00:30:40,830
pray for their hardships.

429
00:30:42,200 --> 00:30:44,910
Because of that, their prayers
sometimes include crying,

430
00:30:45,940 --> 00:30:47,110
screaming,

431
00:30:49,740 --> 00:30:53,810
and sometimes even shrieking.

432
00:30:58,890 --> 00:31:00,390
I saw your brother outside.

433
00:31:01,360 --> 00:31:04,320
Let's come here together next time
to pray together.

434
00:31:13,170 --> 00:31:16,000
We keep receiving things from them.

435
00:31:16,140 --> 00:31:19,470
We should all attend
the service this weekend.

436
00:31:19,540 --> 00:31:23,840
Yes, let's go. Not even siblings
would do this much for each other.

437
00:31:24,380 --> 00:31:26,380
How was school, you guys?

438
00:31:26,550 --> 00:31:28,050
Did you make a lot of new friends?

439
00:31:31,050 --> 00:31:32,690
It was only our first day.

440
00:31:32,750 --> 00:31:34,920
You're right.
There's no need to rush.

441
00:31:35,720 --> 00:31:38,020
Sang-jin, how was your day today?

442
00:31:39,390 --> 00:31:41,390
It... It was nice.

443
00:31:41,660 --> 00:31:44,060
That's good to hear.
I noticed that

444
00:31:44,130 --> 00:31:46,400
people in this town are so nice.

445
00:31:46,470 --> 00:31:48,440
They're so naive and honest.

446
00:31:51,200 --> 00:31:53,870
I'm going to go to bed first.

447
00:31:53,940 --> 00:31:56,280
Why? Do you feel sick?

448
00:31:56,340 --> 00:31:57,980
No, I just don't have an appetite.

449
00:31:58,040 --> 00:32:00,610
But you should still finish
your dinner, Sang-jin.

450
00:32:00,680 --> 00:32:04,350
He's probably tired from having
to adjust to the new environment.

451
00:32:04,750 --> 00:32:07,350
You should sleep in order
to feel better. Rest up.

452
00:32:08,290 --> 00:32:09,320
Okay.

453
00:32:11,630 --> 00:32:15,060
Sang-mi, you should take
good care of Sang-jin.

454
00:32:15,130 --> 00:32:17,530
You should act as his guardian
at school.

455
00:32:18,130 --> 00:32:19,130
Okay?

456
00:32:46,360 --> 00:32:47,360
No, no.

457
00:32:47,430 --> 00:32:50,200
He's going to meet the merchants himself.

458
00:32:50,260 --> 00:32:51,360
Yes, that's right.

459
00:32:51,430 --> 00:32:54,370
Please write a good article
for us today.

460
00:32:54,430 --> 00:32:56,170
-Okay, thanks.
-Is everyone ready?

461
00:32:56,670 --> 00:32:58,670
Sir, it's time for you to go now.

462
00:32:58,870 --> 00:33:02,210
Can you think of another
expression than saying,

463
00:33:02,280 --> 00:33:04,010
"I'll do my best to protect you"?

464
00:33:04,140 --> 00:33:07,510
It just sounds too common.
There's nothing special about this.

465
00:33:09,120 --> 00:33:12,350
"I'll protect you like a father."
How does that sound?

466
00:33:12,720 --> 00:33:13,720
What?

467
00:33:17,460 --> 00:33:19,530
Sang-hwan, wait a moment.

468
00:33:19,590 --> 00:33:21,260
-We don't have much time.
-Just a second.

469
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:24,130
Come here, you punk.

470
00:33:24,200 --> 00:33:25,470
I'm going to be late for school.

471
00:33:26,400 --> 00:33:28,570
Your mom told you to always wear
your necktie properly

472
00:33:28,640 --> 00:33:31,540
regardless of how busy you may be.

473
00:33:33,640 --> 00:33:36,510
Sang-hwan, I know you're already
aware of this,

474
00:33:37,640 --> 00:33:40,980
but I'm going to make sure to become
the governor again,

475
00:33:41,110 --> 00:33:43,150
and I'm going to make
your mom get better.

476
00:33:43,220 --> 00:33:46,190
So please stay out
of trouble until then.

477
00:33:46,550 --> 00:33:49,560
You can do me that much, right?

478
00:33:50,760 --> 00:33:51,860
I'm sorry.

479
00:33:53,290 --> 00:33:54,630
You'll be late for school.

480
00:33:54,760 --> 00:33:56,130
You should be the one to hurry up.

481
00:33:56,230 --> 00:33:57,260
Okay.

482
00:33:58,200 --> 00:33:59,230
Bye.

483
00:34:02,470 --> 00:34:03,770
You should go now.

484
00:34:04,770 --> 00:34:05,770
Okay.

485
00:34:06,710 --> 00:34:08,170
"Like a father".

486
00:34:08,880 --> 00:34:10,739
Let's go with that one.

487
00:34:12,110 --> 00:34:15,820
Confucius thought the root cause
of our world's chaos

488
00:34:15,949 --> 00:34:18,690
was the moral corruption
among humans.

489
00:34:18,989 --> 00:34:20,920
To overcome this,
this is what he said.

490
00:34:21,120 --> 00:34:23,820
He emphasized that we should
become benevolent.

491
00:34:23,889 --> 00:34:26,690
Then let's talk about the core
meaning of our existence.

492
00:34:30,429 --> 00:34:31,429
Listen up.

493
00:34:32,330 --> 00:34:35,300
I heard that some of you frequently go to

494
00:34:35,370 --> 00:34:37,969
billiard rooms and pubs these days.

495
00:34:38,040 --> 00:34:41,310
You know what will happen
if any of you get caught by me, right?

496
00:34:41,409 --> 00:34:42,580
-Yes, ma'am.
-Yes, ma'am.

497
00:34:42,639 --> 00:34:45,949
The ones in charge of cleaning today
are Sang-hwan and Dong-cheol.

498
00:34:46,610 --> 00:34:49,380
I want you guys to clean
the classroom neatly

499
00:34:49,449 --> 00:34:50,880
and come to me for a checkup
before you go home.

500
00:34:51,020 --> 00:34:52,020
-Okay, ma'am.
-Okay, ma'am.

501
00:34:52,090 --> 00:34:53,090
See you guys.

502
00:35:04,630 --> 00:35:05,630
Hey.

503
00:35:13,040 --> 00:35:15,040
Ready or not, rock-paper-scissors.

504
00:35:15,340 --> 00:35:17,380
-Rock-paper-scissors.
-Rock-paper-scissors.

505
00:35:19,380 --> 00:35:20,410
I wish you all the best.

506
00:35:20,480 --> 00:35:21,850
Please help me, sir.

507
00:35:23,480 --> 00:35:26,890
Come on. Come on.

508
00:35:26,950 --> 00:35:28,720
Forget it. You can play by yourself.

509
00:35:30,460 --> 00:35:32,660
My gosh, what's taking them so long?

510
00:35:37,600 --> 00:35:40,170
Isn't she that girl from Seoul?
She is.

511
00:35:40,500 --> 00:35:42,100
-Is she waiting for someone?
-Watch out.

512
00:35:42,170 --> 00:35:43,200
For what?

513
00:35:44,740 --> 00:35:45,740
Hey!

514
00:35:46,840 --> 00:35:48,910
You could've warned me.

515
00:35:48,980 --> 00:35:50,740
I told you to watch out.

516
00:35:51,110 --> 00:35:52,110
Really?

517
00:35:52,450 --> 00:35:54,080
Shouldn't we tell the teacher?

518
00:35:54,150 --> 00:35:55,720
